==Funding==
Power Ledger succesfully raised A$17million (~13.21 million U$ as per 6th of October 2017) during the Pre-ICO at the beginning of September 2017. 
In the following Main Sale, the company raised another A$17million 
(A$6million in Bitcoin, A$10.7million in Ether and a$0.4million in Litecoin). <ref name="Medium1"/> 
The price per POWR token was 0.0838 USD during the Pre-Sale.<ref name="ICOdrop">https://icodrops.com/powerledger/, accessed on 21.07.2018.</ref> 
There were a total of 1,000,000,000 POWR token issued, whereof 350,000 were sold during the ICO. Power Ledger keeps 250,000 POWR in escrow for two years. Thereafter they can be used for additional funding rounds.
<ref name="ICO">https://tge.powerledger.io/media/Power-Ledger-TGE-Token-Paper.pdf, accessed on 21.07.2018.</ref>

In November 2017 the australian government granted A$8million to a project in the city of freemantel. Power Ledger is providing 
the blockchain technology for this project. It is however unclear which share of the A$8million were granted to Power Ledger. 
<ref>https://medium.com/power-ledger/australian-government-awards-grant-to-8-million-project-in-the-city-of-fremantle-using-the-power-2dbadfad50ae, accessed on 21.07.2018.</ref>

